JamesPearceLFC: &quot;I know that money is tight in the current climate, but I couldn't help but come away from Sunday thinking - 'Liverpool need someone for the next 3/4 months -  if that means a loan signing or a free agent, so be it.'&quot; [the red agenda podcast]<br />
<br />
&quot;We're not looking for the next Virgil van Dijk, we're just looking for someone who's better than what Klopp already has, and with the greatest respect, that shouldn't be too difficult to find. I really do hope Liverpool reassess their options.&quot;

